this is OK as the error handler will ignore a null status  but that was not obvious - we will need another comment

The Code Formatter currently has an option for "Blank lines within class declarations, Before first declaration" but it has no option for "After last declaration."

Consider the following code:

public class A {
    public void f() {
    }
}


The Code Formatter can add a blank line before the method, but it cannot add one after the method.

This is the intended result:

public class A {

    public void f() {
    }

}


This is the actual result:

public class A {

    public void f() {
    }
}


This is an enhancement request to add a new option within the "Blank lines within class declarations" section for "After last declaration" or equivalently "Before closing brace."

